on other boats in the past.

31:19.129 --> 31:20.714
Oh!

31:23.341 --> 31:25.635
All right. Yeah. Where’s those
little white things?

31:25.677 --> 31:29.347
I will get you two.
Yes.

31:33.560 --> 31:35.020
Excited.

31:38.189 --> 31:40.525
Do you mind if I borrow
this for a second?

31:40.567 --> 31:42.318
-You have to do it.
-No.

31:43.236 --> 31:44.779
Why have I got roped into it?

31:44.821 --> 31:46.197
Look at a ----ing
Luka and Max.

31:46.239 --> 31:47.282
They’re models, for God’s sake.

31:47.323 --> 31:49.075
Shimmy, shimmy,
yeah, yeah.

31:49.117 --> 31:51.327
I’m a lot of things, but
I’m not a ----ing model.

31:51.369 --> 31:52.328
[trilling]

31:52.370 --> 31:53.913
The guys are coming.
Here we go.

31:53.955 --> 31:54.914
Hot baby.

31:54.956 --> 31:56.708
[trilling]

32:12.140 --> 32:13.016
The guys are coming,
here we go.

32:13.600 --> 32:15.018
Hey, baby!

32:15.060 --> 32:16.686
[shouting]

32:21.149 --> 32:25.320
If I take my clothes off,
it might hurt the tip.

32:30.658 --> 32:32.243
Hey, hey, oh!

32:36.581 --> 32:38.625
Hello.

32:38.667 --> 32:40.418
Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

32:41.920 --> 32:44.339
Luka is a very attractive man.

32:44.381 --> 32:45.757
Thank you!

32:45.799 --> 32:48.885
It’s been a while since
I’ve seen things that hot.

32:48.927 --> 32:51.429
Oh, my God, how funny is that?

32:51.471 --> 32:53.181
Oh, my God!

32:53.223 --> 32:55.141
Now I’m going to bed.

32:55.892 --> 32:58.395
Party in my room.

32:58.436 --> 32:59.771
Okay, I need to go to bed.

33:01.606 --> 33:04.192
When you take this down
to laundry before you go,

33:04.234 --> 33:07.362
just label tablecloth.

33:07.404 --> 33:08.697
[laughing]

33:10.907 --> 33:13.910
-I’ll see you tomorrow.
-See you later.

33:13.952 --> 33:15.245
Good night.

33:21.501 --> 33:23.586
Sh--.

33:23.628 --> 33:26.172
-No, way.
-No, way.

33:27.966 --> 33:30.218
I think Jess is super easygoing.

33:30.260 --> 33:31.636
Kind of like me,
like just chill.

33:34.222 --> 33:36.099
Maybe a little bit shy.

33:36.141 --> 33:37.726
She’s not in
an open relationship,

33:37.767 --> 33:38.893
which is a good sign.

33:38.935 --> 33:41.187
I just want to cuddle, bro.

33:44.774 --> 33:46.484
-Goodbye.
-Bye.

33:49.070 --> 33:50.363
[alarm sounds]

33:58.163 --> 33:59.330
I love these.

33:59.372 --> 34:00.373
These look so numa.

34:00.415 --> 34:02.625
-You ready to party?
-No.

34:02.667 --> 34:04.127
Morning.

34:04.169 --> 34:08.423
[rooster crows]

34:08.465 --> 34:11.217
You know the guys who’s making
a turururu with a snake?

34:12.677 --> 34:15.096
[vocalizing]

34:15.138 --> 34:17.349
It’s our last meal here.

34:17.390 --> 34:18.683
Right?

34:26.024 --> 34:28.234
The chef special
is omelette anyway.

34:28.276 --> 34:29.569
By the bar.

34:29.611 --> 34:31.321
Thank you.

34:43.958 --> 34:45.543
Come, chef.
No break.

34:45.585 --> 34:47.629
I ain’t took
one break all season.

34:47.671 --> 34:48.713
Oh.

34:52.384 --> 34:54.386
It’s just prima donna stuff.

34:54.427 --> 34:55.428
We see this all the time.

34:55.470 --> 34:57.931
My last boat, every evening,

34:57.972 --> 34:59.182
this guy would
come in the gallery

34:59.224 --> 35:00.684
and he’d be like,
can I have raspberries?

35:00.725 --> 35:02.060
There was raspberries
all over the sheet.

35:02.102 --> 35:03.853
I don’t know if it was fetish,

35:03.895 --> 35:06.356
if they were bumping and
grinding with the raspberries,

35:06.398 --> 35:07.732
because it was everywhere.

35:07.774 --> 35:09.359
That and coconut oil.

35:11.695 --> 35:12.946
Put up her ass, clearly.

35:12.987 --> 35:14.906
[laughing]

35:16.491 --> 35:17.826
Mm mm mm.

35:17.867 --> 35:19.327
Lara, Lara, Max, Max.

35:19.369 --> 35:20.704
Can you guys head up to the bow?

35:20.745 --> 35:25.583
And we’re just going to
pull in the passarelle.

35:25.625 --> 35:27.168
-Prepare everything?
-Prepare everything.

35:27.210 --> 35:29.546
Free the lines, start taking
it on the anchor.

35:29.587 --> 35:32.215
Okay, copy.

35:32.257 --> 35:33.925
All lines are free.

35:36.261 --> 35:38.304
Here we go.

35:38.346 --> 35:39.764
Luka, Luka, talk to me.

35:39.806 --> 35:42.684
We’ve got to go another
15 meters starboard side.

35:42.726 --> 35:46.354
You have some small boats coming
down your starboard side.

35:46.396 --> 35:48.440
Seven meters on your port side.

35:48.481 --> 35:50.442
Portofino is like
playing Frogger.

35:50.483 --> 35:51.735
Boat’s coming port side.

35:51.776 --> 35:53.611
There’s boats
coming starboard side.

35:53.653 --> 35:55.572
What the [bleep] is going on?

35:55.613 --> 35:57.907
Dude, these people
are so ruthless.

35:57.949 --> 35:59.784
Nine meters on your port side.

35:59.826 --> 36:00.952
Like yelling about us.

36:00.994 --> 36:02.746
You know how New York taxis
used to be?

36:02.787 --> 36:04.247
That’s Portofino.

36:04.289 --> 36:05.749
It can be a huge distraction,

36:05.790 --> 36:09.252
but for me, all I see
is navigation.

36:09.294 --> 36:12.088
25 meters to the boats
on your starboard side.

36:12.130 --> 36:13.131
Secure the anchor.

36:13.173 --> 36:16.384
-Okay.
-Anchor on.

36:16.426 --> 36:18.094
And your port quarter
is all clear.

36:18.136 --> 36:19.929
-Ciao. Grazie.
-How are you?

36:19.971 --> 36:21.222
-Well done, bro.
-Bravo.

36:21.264 --> 36:22.557
Nice line.

36:22.599 --> 36:24.059
And we’re on the move.

36:26.770 --> 36:29.105
-All right, me love.
-This is Captain Sandy’s.

36:29.147 --> 36:30.190
Perfect.

36:30.231 --> 36:31.274
There is some more stuff
in here, though.

36:31.316 --> 36:32.484
How’s that possible?

36:32.525 --> 36:33.610
-Then what’s this sheet for?
-I...

36:33.651 --> 36:34.986
Okay, I’m hella
confused, girls.

36:35.028 --> 36:36.363
Why?

36:36.404 --> 36:37.864
Because you gave me
this because it’s Sandy’s.

36:37.906 --> 36:39.407
What’s that, then?
Sandy’s was too big.

36:39.449 --> 36:41.076
I handled it in two washes.

36:41.117 --> 36:42.952
No, but I’ve got a fitted sheet.
There’s another fitted sheet.

36:42.994 --> 36:44.454
-No, that wasn’t a sheet.
-Was it a mattress protector?

36:44.496 --> 36:45.497
Yes.

36:45.538 --> 36:46.498
So mattress protector,
right here,

36:46.539 --> 36:49.834
then I can take everything.

36:56.257 --> 36:57.676
No, no, there’s some
more stuff in there.

36:57.717 --> 36:59.135
I know, babe.
Hear me out.

36:59.177 --> 37:00.512
Yeah.

37:00.553 --> 37:02.806
Once the mattress protector
comes out with a towel,

37:02.847 --> 37:04.599
I will take the whole
package up to her.

37:04.641 --> 37:05.975
-Yeah.
-But for now,

37:06.017 --> 37:07.852
if you can finish those cabins,
that’ll be fab.

37:07.894 --> 37:09.813
I would assume the
laundry’s a safer spot

37:09.854 --> 37:11.314
for someone who’s
not really familiar

37:11.356 --> 37:12.691
with such a big boat.

37:12.732 --> 37:14.484
And I’m thinking,
where else can we put Lily?

37:14.526 --> 37:16.861
Is this basically the luggage
compartment at this point?

37:21.783 --> 37:23.118
Coming up...

37:27.997 --> 37:31.334
He wasn’t so brave
without you, but now he is.

37:38.049 --> 37:38.842
Okay, I’m heading to the bow.

37:39.426 --> 37:41.511
Ay, ay, ay, ay.

37:41.553 --> 37:42.721
That’s when I put on extra dry.

37:42.762 --> 37:44.556
That’s when I take out your...

37:44.597 --> 37:46.725
-She forgot a lot of clothes.
-Yeah, she did.

37:46.766 --> 37:49.019
Deck crew,
prepare the anchor.

37:49.060 --> 37:50.020
Copy that.

37:50.061 --> 37:51.229
I think we go in
between those two.

37:51.271 --> 37:52.689
-You got this.
-Okay.

37:52.731 --> 37:56.484
Dropping!

37:56.526 --> 37:58.862
Yeah, 45 meters to the dock.

37:58.903 --> 38:00.572
Lock that one off,
Haley, and throw the others.

38:00.613 --> 38:03.241
That’s all of our
stern lines connected.

38:03.283 --> 38:04.909
Nice work, everybody.

38:05.618 --> 38:07.162
Packing is the worst.

38:07.203 --> 38:08.163
Let me know if you need help.

38:08.204 --> 38:09.748
I need a lot of help.

38:09.789 --> 38:12.083
All crew, let’s meet on the
dock for guest departure.

38:18.298 --> 38:19.924
-Want help down?
-Thank you.

38:19.966 --> 38:23.094
